Function [CC]: FUNCTION: Removal of H(2)O(2), oxidation of toxic reductants, biosynthesis and degradation of lignin, suberization, auxin catabolism, response to environmental stresses such as wounding, pathogen attack and oxidative stress. These functions might be dependent on each isozyme/isoform in each plant tissue. {ECO:0000256|ARBA:ARBA00002322}.
Gene ontology (GO): extracellular region [GO:0005576]; heme binding [GO:0020037]; metal ion binding [GO:0046872]; peroxidase activity [GO:0004601]; hydrogen peroxide catabolic process [GO:0042744]; response to oxidative stress [GO:0006979]
Protein families: Peroxidase family, Ascorbate peroxidase subfamily; Peroxidase family, Classical plant (class III) peroxidase subfamily

Function [CC]: FUNCTION: Involved in the hydrocarbon hydroxylating system, which transfers electrons from NADH to rubredoxin reductase and then through rubredoxin to alkane 1 monooxygenase. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:12730186, ECO:0000269|PubMed:14574114}.
Gene ontology (GO): cytoplasm [GO:0005737]; flavin adenine dinucleotide binding [GO:0050660]; rubredoxin-NAD+ reductase activity [GO:0015044]; rubredoxin-NADP+ reductase activity [GO:0015046]; alkane catabolic process [GO:0043448]

Protein names: Leaf-branch compost cutinase (LC-cutinase) (LCC) (EC 3.1.1.74) (PET-digesting enzyme) (Poly(ethylene terephthalate) hydrolase) (PET hydrolase) (PETase) (EC 3.1.1.101)
Function [CC]: FUNCTION: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of cutin, a polyester that forms the structure of plant cuticle (PubMed:22194294). Shows esterase activity towards p-nitrophenol-linked aliphatic esters (pNP-aliphatic esters), with a preference for short-chain substrates (C4 substrate at most) (PubMed:22194294, PubMed:24593046). Cannot hydrolyze olive oil (PubMed:22194294). Is also able to degrade poly(ethylene terephthalate), the most abundant polyester plastic in the world (PubMed:22194294, PubMed:32269349). Can also depolymerize poly(epsilon-caprolactone) (PCL), a synthetic aliphatic biodegradable polyester (PubMed:22194294). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:22194294, ECO:0000269|PubMed:24593046, ECO:0000269|PubMed:32269349}.
Gene ontology (GO): extracellular region [GO:0005576]; acetylesterase activity [GO:0008126]; cutinase activity [GO:0050525]

Protein names: Manganese peroxidase 1 (MnP-1) (MnP1) (EC 1.11.1.13) (Manganese peroxidase isozyme 1) (Peroxidase manganese-dependent 1) (Peroxidase manganese-dependent I)
Function [CC]: FUNCTION: Catalyzes the oxidation of Mn(2+) to Mn(3+). The latter, acting as a diffusible redox mediator, is capable of oxidizing a variety of lignin compounds.
